results.name: Smallest number which when written in binary contains the binary strings for the numbers 1..n.
comment: All terms belong to A261467. - _Rémy Sigrist_, May 11 2021
example: a(6)=44 because 101100 (44 in base 2) is the smallest number that contains 1, 10, 11, 100, 101 and 110 (1 through 6 in base 2)
results.author: Fred J. Schalekamp, Aug 15 2000
